<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Sunday news bits from Abashi</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=211899" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010537.html">VI = Very Irresponcible</a></B><P>

My compnay let us off early on Friday for the long weekend, so I went home and played some Everquest before dinner.<P>

<B>My company let us off early for the weekend as well :) I believe that the only patch that went up was a new patch program to enable some more verbose file checking.<P>

Previously, we'd heard of some people experience some file corruption problems that aren't caught by the standard version-control procedure. This patch gives an option for a more thorough check (a full CRC check) on the installed files. In other words it should not longer be necessary for tech support to recommend a full re-install to people who are reporting strange problems.<P>

The patch shouldn't at all affect gameplay, so there's really no issue with the timing for when it was put up. I'm sorry you are upset, but did this patch reduce your ability to play the game at all?<P>

Well I should mention that the patch should have been accompanied by a thoroughly descriptive patch message explaining what it was about. I'll see about that on Tuesday.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010570.html">Thoughts on the 3D engine</a></B><P>

Since the graphics engine should be entirely abstract from any gameplay and networking (for the most part) issues why cant the engine simply be upgraded and the old engine still be available for those who use lesser hardware.<P>

<B>It's not so much "can't" as it is "can't feasibly be done with reasonable time and resources". The art used in EverQuest represents nearly 4 years of work for a team of artists. Going through and revamping all of EQ proper with updated textures would take roughly half that time for a full team. Now, if you are talking about a completely new engine, it would then take additional man-years of work by programmers.<P>

New zone geometry, though not being possible for a platform that has to be backward compatible for people using the current engine, would have to match up in every way at every coordinate, so there wouldn't be much of a benefit there either.<P>

Basically, it's not feasible because by the time we'd get EQ rebuilt in the suggested fashion, all of the next-generation games would be out, and we'd have an old game with a fresh look. We'd rather, when that time comes, have a new game with a fresh look.<P>

-Gordon</b><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010233.html">The boats are still slow, I still haven't gotten an official response</a></B><P>

I am suggesting a fix the EXTREMELY LONG AND BORING BOAT RIDE THAT IS UNNECESSARY.<P>

<B>Even though he posted it in jest, Dranthor's reply is pretty much right on target. The length of the boat rides are indeed related to adding some realism to the process. If we'd wanted something akin to teleports from one continent to the other, we would have went that route. The second thing about class-interdependence is also right on target. If the boat rides are too long, you have a method at your disposal to reduce the amount of time taken for travel.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010503.html">...but NOoooo, we don't need an RP Server...</a></B><P>

When I first made Nena she had a background, as story, and actual parents. She was the daughter of my now deleted mage and a wonderful now also deleted half elf rogue. The day the mage informed the half elf that Nena was engaged to marry a high elf enchanter, he proceeded to throw a tantrum that would make any rant hall regular proud. It was all RP'd - all about how no daughter of his would marry some weak chinned bleach blonde high elf. He never said a word about anyone by name (in actuallity he also played the enchanter in question), he never used vulgar language, and for the most part we drew a large crowd that seemed
entertained by the whole thing. All except for the high elf that petitioned him for being offensive and for "spamming" (the conversation was held on a platform in kelethin, away from a lift, in standard /say -not ooc'd or shouted to the zone), and the responding guide agreed! He was told he was given a warning and that any future offenses could result in a banning of his account.<P>

<B>I really think that there must be more to this story. Any time I see something presented that makes it appear that the action taken by a CS Rep was so blatantly wrong, I have to question what really happened. Afterall, were it so clear when it occurred, there's no way that the person would have been warned.<p>

You have the story quoted, so I'm assuming it was written by someone else. Please have the author kick me his station name at <A href="mailto:gwrinn@verant.com">gwrinn@verant.com</a>. I'd like to look into it.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

When the forum_faq came out and I saw they'd removed the initials for Role Play, calling EverQuest a MMOG (as opposed to MMORPG), it just confirmed what I already knew.<P>

<B>You're reading a bit too much into it.<P>

And MMOG is just a broader description of what we make. Yes, EverQuest is an MMORPG. Sovereign will be a MMORTS. We have a MMOAG (action game) in development that we haven't announced yet (other than the fact that we have one in development). We have a couple other MMORPGs in development as well. Whether MMORPG, MMORTS, MMOAG, or MMO-anything, they are all MMOGs, and that's what we do.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010560.html">Gordon- Something that could improve EQ morale BIG time</a></B><P>

At the place a poll would be, put up a little box that says : "What could we (Verant) do to improve YOUR Everquest experience?" Plain and simple. Pretty much like a suggestion card at a restruant.<P>

<B>The poll question you suggest is pretty broad and would be hard to cover in a multiple-choice poll. Of course we could open it up to text, but that's basically what these boards are used for.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010627.html">Thorough File Check. Violation of my personal rights?</a></B><P>

The program is more than likely doing a full CRC of every file in the EQ directory, and checking it with a server version of the CRC. The complexity of the check is likely the cause, and it could also be your computer's speed.<P>

<B>Indeed. Pressing the button issues a full CRC check of every file on the required files list for EverQuest and downloads a new version if the local and remote CRCs differ. We found that a few people were suffering some file corruption that wasn't being noticed by our normal method of version control, so implemented this method for those cases.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010564.html">Necromancers and the resisted unresistable lifetaps</a></B><P>

Now I know I heard somewhere that lifetaps weren't completely unresistable but they were darn near close. <P>

<B>The resistability or lack thereof of any spell is subject to the immunity of the target. In other words, even the "nearly unresistable" lifetap isn't going to work against a creature that is immune to magic.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/010571.html">Was there ever an official response to the horse idea?</a></B><P>

I saw at one time a bunch of posts concerning the possibilty of adding horses to the game. I know that the graphic is already there for mob's so that part wouldn't be all that hard to do. <P>

<B>Yes, we've responded to the request recently and in the past. Horses won't be a feature that we'll see in EverQuest. I'll see about putting this in the next version of the forum FAQ.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/008565.html">Abashi - Hasten Bootstrider and Brother Zephyl should not be mutual Placeholders</a></B><P>

This would be fine by me if Hasten were not a PH for Brother Zephyl. Both of these mobs are required for major quests, they should not be placeholders for each other. <P>

<B>I do understand the desire to complete both quests as soon as one has all of the quest items for either. That said it's not really something that we're planning to change. People are completing both quests, and the items to be garnered from either are nice enough to warrant an added level of difficulty. <P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
